Commentary: first-ball drop! Put down by Azhar Ali at second slip. Particularly difficult chance. He dives full-length to his wrong side - his left - and the ball does not stick. Swing for Amir right away. Full awayswinger, starts outside off, and curls away further. Warner has a bigger swing at it. Slashes hard and sends an outside edge. Azhar dives to his left, attempts the catch with both hands, but it pops out
good length and holds its line outside off, left alone

Commentary: length ball, angled in, and then shapes away. Head has a crease-bound waft and watches the ball pass the outside edge
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Head, no run

Commentary: beaten again! Good length, angled in, and the late swing takes the ball away from the left-hander. He pokes, playing for the angle, and misses
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Head, no run

Commentary: length and outside off, guided towards point with soft hands
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Head, no run

Commentary: full and angled in on off, Warner is on the move as he pushes towards mid-off.

Commentary: length and outside off, hint of extra bounce, Head rides it and glides a single in the direction of third man

length ball on off played back to the bowler

Commentary: outswinger, full, starts outside off and moves away. Head leaves it be

Commentary: good length and holds its line just outside off, Head ushers it through to the keeper

short, the length is there for a cut, but the line is too close to off. Chopped away square on the off side

and there it is! A century off 78 balls. Fullish on off stump and he plays a defensive push into the off side, not too far from the finish of Junaid's follow-through, but both he and Head take off immediately to ensure they complete the quick single with ease. This is his fastest hundred in ODIs - his previous quickest was off 92 balls

Amir runs in from long-on, the sun squinting in his eyes, but shells it. Pops in and out. The camera pans out to coach Arthur and fielding coach Rixon in the Pakistan change room. overpitched and outside off, flat-batted drive to the right of extra cover
pitched up on middle, Head stays leg-side of the ball and punches it to mid-off. Pinches a quick single
full and on leg stump, Warner now stays leg-side of the ball and chips it in the air. Well-controlled hit, scooped over wide mid-off. One-bounce four
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Warner, FOUR runs

Commentary: chest-high short ball on the leg stump, Warner is unperturbed. He rocks back and hooks it over long leg. This one goes all the way
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Warner, SIX runs

Commentary: full and outside off. Flat-batted away fiercely to the right of mid-off
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Warner, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length and on the hips, Warner camps on the back foot and clips it away through square leg
Warner deftly runs it down to third man and brings up his 150. He raises his bat and acknowledges the applause again. Is the 200 on? His third fifty has come off only 29 balls
Warner gently drops the ball to the leg side for a single
dug short and outside off, sits up to be hit. Head rocks back and pulls along the ground to deep midwicket
Warner backs away outside leg stump, Wahab spears it wide outside off, 150ks. Warner slashes but can't reach it
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Warner, no run

Commentary: yorker on middle, 150.1ks, pace like fire. Warner jams his bat down in the nick of time. Squirts a bottom edge behind square on the leg side
bouncer outside off, bursts off the surface, beats the hook
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Head, no run

Commentary: yorker on the leg stump, squeezed out to midwicket, where Umar Akmal is lazy to bend down and fumbles an extra run
slower short ball outside off, waits for the ball to arrive and drags the ball to deep midwicket
very full and outside off, near yorker, front-foot drive straight to mid-off
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Head, no run

Commentary: tennis-ball bouncer outside off,  Head attempts a ramp but the ball bounces over
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Head, no run

Commentary: length and outside off, helped down to third man
Junaid digs another slower bouncer outside off, Warner jumps off his feet, upper-cuts, but the ball still sails over him to the keeper
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Warner, no run

Commentary: yorker on middle, Warner stays leg-side of the ball and digs it back to the bowler's right. He fumbles, and this is now Australia's highest opening stand in ODIs, surpassing Finch and S Marsh's effort in 2013
very full on the stumps, Warner picks it up and whips it in the air just over midwicket
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Warner, FOUR runs

Commentary: fractionally short and outside off, Warner short-arms it away to long-on
Head dances out, takes a half-volley and drills it down the ground. There is a misfield at long-on, but it's just two
Head moves away outside leg stump, the bowler follows him. Nicked in front of the keeper as he is cramped for room
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Head, no run

Commentary: Head walks across off, meets a full-toss, and slaps it down the ground to long-on

there it is! Slower short ball on middle, Warner waits for the ball to arrive. Then launches it into the stands beyond midwicket with a pull. This is now Australia's highest stand for any wicket in ODIs
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Warner, SIX runs

Commentary: short and slides in with the arm on middle from around the stumps, Head goes back and forces it to Hafeez
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hafeez to Head, no run

Commentary: dropped short on middle, Head skips back and pulls firmly through the leg side. Deep midwicket slides to his right, just escorts the ball to the fence
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hafeez to Head, FOUR runs
Mohammad Hafeez to Head, no run

Commentary: length ball, looped up outside off, gets forward and drives down to long-off
Warner steps away, makes room, and cuts a short ball to sweeper cover
length-ball offbreak outside off, turns away, tapped to the off side
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hafeez to Head, no run

Commentary: wide yorker outside off, Warner can't scythe it away. Beaten
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Warner, no run

Commentary: very full and outside off, Warner opens the bat-face and squeezes a single down to third man
slower short ball outside off, Head reaches out, slashes and does not make contact
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Head, no run

Commentary: wide yorker, reaches out and slices the ball in the direction of point

Warner uses his feet, wide full ball outside off, Warner squeezes his bat down, but can't make contact. The ball whistles past the outside edge. Junaid appeals, thinking Warner had nicked it. The appeal is shot down quickly
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Warner, no run

Commentary: Junaid persists with the wide yorker, Warner aims to reach out and carve it away. No dice. Instead he is floored
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Warner, no run

Commentary: dropped short and just a shade outside off, moves back and pulls firmly to long-on
speared short on middle, goes back and flat-bats it to the bowler's right
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, no run

Commentary: Hafeez tosses it up full outside off, Warner reaches out his hands and smacks it over extra cover for six. He then loses his balance; he's suffering from cramps
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hafeez to Warner, SIX runs

Commentary: pushed through on middle, driven down to long-off

Head removes his helmet, kisses it, and gets a hug from Warner. Soaks in his maiden ODI hundred, on his home ground. And he reaches the landmark with his favourite cut. Short and outside off, cracked away through the covers
Warner ventures to the leg side, Hafeez follows him and tucks him up. Punched down the ground for a single
full-toss outside off, Warner creams a drive to the right of sweeper cover. Skips away to the fence
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Warner, FOUR runs

Commentary: wide yorker, that's very harsh on Junaid. Inside the tramline. Speared outside off, Warner can't reach out and touch it
very full and outside off, flat-batted away to cover
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Warner, no run

Commentary: carved away in the air. It dies in front of point, but Azam bends forward and snaps up a low catch. He claims it, and they go upstairs. It's a clean catch and a cramping David Warner walks back for 179, his best ODI score. No double-hundred for him, though. Slower short ball, cuts away from Warner. He reaches out for the ball and scythes it in the air. The opening stand ends on 284
Dismissal_text: DA Warner c Babar Azam b Junaid Khan 179 (186m 128b 19x4 5x6) SR: 139.84

Commentary: and he sets to work with a first-ball four. Back of a length and angling away outside off, steps back and punches it serenely through the covers
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Smith, FOUR runs

Commentary: Swatted away in the air. Wahab tracks the ball from mid-on, runs to his right, and plucks the overhead catch. But on impact his right knee got jarred in the turf. He collapses and winces in pain. Banged in short and outside off head-hunting ball, too high for a hook. Smith flat-bats it in the air and holes out
Dismissal_text: SPD Smith c Wahab Riaz b Junaid Khan 4 (3m 2b 1x4 0x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: yorker on the leg stump, dug back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Head, no run

Commentary: back of a length and on leg stump, Maxwell steps away outside leg and hits to wide long-on with a clubbing swing
Head backs away outside leg, this is a head-high bouncer outside off. Head jumps off the ground but the ball sails over him. Wide called
Head pre-meditates outside leg, Amir chases the batsman with a 142ks short ball.Head smites a six over midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Head, SIX runs

Commentary: Head pre-mediates again, backing a long way outside leg. Amir hurls it wide outside off. Head can't reach out and flay it away. Beaten
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Head, no run

Commentary: low full toss on leg stump, scooped in front of mid-off
very full on leg stump, 144.3ks, Maxwell shovels it away to cow corner
pretty full and wide outside off, Head throws his bat at ball and slices an outside edge to third man. 300 up for the hosts
147ks full-toss on middle and leg. Head has a good ol' hack at it and drags it to midwicket off the inside half. Wahab working up serious pace, despite hurting his knee
Maxwell shuffles across off, banged in short, Maxwell half-ducks, the ball flies over him. Wide called for height

151.7ks, short and wide outside off, Maxwell, having backed away outside leg, has ample leverage to flat-bat a cut over point. Hit flat and hard for six. In the World Cup 2015 match, Maxwell unleashed the back-away-look-away cut off Wahab. This one was the back-away-look-at-the-ball cut
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Maxwell, SIX runs

Commentary: pinpoint yorker, dug back to the bowler
full on middle, Head backs away and lifts the ball over mid-off
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Head, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker on middle, drilled down to mid-on
Maxwell shuffles across off stump, Wahab slips in the slower cutter at 115ks. Maxwell adjusts and helps it away fine on the leg side
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Maxwell, FOUR runs

Commentary: nice and full outside off, Head looks to launch it downtown. Does not time it well enough, scoops the ball over Azhar at mid-off

high short ball outside off, Head has a crack at it with the pull. Skies over midwicket. Sharjeel at deep midwicket runs across to his right, puts in the dive, but the ball eludes his reach. Long-on runs to his left and mops it up
full-toss on middle and leg, Head has a swipe at it and ends up dragging the ball off the inside half to deep midwicket
full and wide outside off, 145.6ks, Maxwell, having backed away, can't put bat on ball
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Maxwell, no run

Commentary: Maxwell hits it flat and hard to Hafeez at sweeper cover.  Full and outside off, Maxwell simply shovels it in the air with the bottom hand to the man in the deep. Dolly catch
Dismissal_text: GJ Maxwell c Mohammad Hafeez b Mohammad Amir 13 (16m 7b 1x4 1x6) SR: 185.71

Commentary: length ball on middle and leg, clipped away to Azam at deep midwicket. Azam picks the ball up swiftly and releases it to Amir, but the bowler does not collect the ball cleanly, messing up a run-out opportunity. Head is home at the non-striker's end and Wade pockets two
full-toss on leg stump, 148.2ks, whipped away to deep square leg
wild short ball outside off, slanted away further. Wide called
low full-toss on off, Wade threads the gap between wide mid-off and extra-cover with a good-looking drive
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Wade, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower short ball just outside off, legcutter, Wade bails out of the pull. Floats through to the keeper and beats Rizwan
Head backs away outside leg, takes a full ball from leg stump and hoicks it away to deep midwicket
length ball on middle and leg, driven to long-on. Wade calls for two and gets it in the end
yorker on off, 147.2ks, squeezed back to Wahab
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Wade, no run

Commentary: starts off with a yorker just outside off, jabbed into the cover-point region for a single
slower ball from Hasan. Full and cuts away from the left-hander. Wade aims to loft it, possibly down the ground. Ends up slicing a catch to sweeper cover
Dismissal_text: MS Wade c Shoaib Malik b Hasan Ali 8 (8m 6b 1x4 0x6) SR: 133.33

Commentary: Head puts Hasan in the stands beyond midwicket. Length ball outside off, another slower one, drops down to one knee and smites a slog-sweep
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Head, SIX runs

Commentary: Juggles and takes it on the third attempt. Azhar has a wry smile. Head walks back for 128, acknowledging the applause at his home ground. Full and angling away outside off, Head eyes a leg-side slog, ends up skying an overhead catch to long-off. Azhar hangs onto it.... just
Dismissal_text: TM Head c Azhar Ali b Hasan Ali 128 (219m 137b 9x4 3x6) SR: 93.43

Commentary: Faulkner steps down the track, Hasan pulls his length back outside off and beats him. The new man slashes and does not connect
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Faulkner, no run

Commentary: very full and wide outside off, on the tramline or just inside, wide called. Faulkner can't carve it away
low full-toss on off, jabbed into the covers
short on middle and leg, cramps Faulkner for room. Dabbed towards point
dug short and outside off, dragged to midwicket off the inside half
full cutter outside off, Faulkner swings way too early and misses
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Faulkner, no run

Commentary: slower bouncer outside off, Faulkner has a swat at it and top-edges it away to the right of deep square leg. Hafeez moves to his right, is lazy to bend down as he looks to scoop it back into the field of play. Instead, escorts the ball to the boundary
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Faulkner, FOUR runs

Commentary: wide yorker outside off, Faulkner can't jam it out. He calls his partner through for a bye. Handscomb makes it even as Rizwan connects with the direct hit at the striker's end

slower short ball on the leg stump, Handscomb does not get enough power behind the pull. He can't manufacture his own pace. Holes out to Hafeez at deep square leg running across to his left. Wahab finishes with a wicket. He has done fairly well today even as his colleagues crashed and burned
Dismissal_text: PSP Handscomb c Mohammad Hafeez b Wahab Riaz 1 (10m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: yorker on off, Starc can only squeeze it through cover
full and outside off, Faulkner lays into it, smearing a drive wide of sweeper
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Faulkner, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker just outside off, Faulkner jams his bat down on it. Breaks the inside of the bat, and Faulkner needs a new one. Hasan picks the ball up in his follow-through and scoops it onto the stumps, but Faulkner is well in
yorker just outside off, angled down to third man
full on the stumps, dug back to the bowler, who has an aim at the non-striker's end with Faulkner backing up. He is in, though
slower one outside off, slashes an outside edge down to third man. Good running - two
yorker, swerves in on off, inside-edged onto the pad, as the ball wanders away to the off side
yorker on leg stump, squeezed square through the leg side for a double
another yorker, which is jammed out for one

very full and outside off, shovelled with the bottom hand to wide long-on. Starc and Faulkner push on for the second. Nice, flat throw from the deep to Rizwan who breaks the stumps and catches Starc short
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Starc, 1 run, OUT
Dismissal_text: MA Starc run out (†Mohammad Rizwan/Shoaib Malik) 6 (8m 5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 120.00

Commentary: full-toss on off, scooped in front of cover as the leg-side slog goes wrong
very full on middle, whipped or rather toe-ended to short fine leg
a wide to start with, swinging too far down the leg side as Azhar looks to flick
fullish outside off, Azhar plays a checked drive into the gap between cover and mid-off
no swing this time, goes with the angle down the leg side and hits the left-hander's front pad as he misses the flick
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: this one does swing away in the corridor. No feet from Sharjeel, just a tentative play and miss
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: another wide. Starc slants this a long way down the leg side. Sharjeel swivels to try and pull, but no way is he meeting that
short, rising over off stump. Not too much room to free his arms through the pull, so he plays a short-arm checked pull into the gap to the right of square leg
this one isn't short enough to pull, hits him on the stomach as he attempts the shot anyway
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: lovely. Fullish, swinging away on a sixth-stump line, inviting the drive away from the body. Sharjeel plays and misses again. Needs a bigger stride forward to drive those
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: length ball in the corridor, a bit of away-swerve. Azhar leaves it alone
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Azhar Ali, no run

Commentary: ooh, this one swings even further, from slightly wider outside off. Azhar pokes at it, playing a half-hearted back-foot punch, and misses by a long way
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Azhar Ali, no run

Commentary: length ball close to off stump, nicely done. Plays a soft-hands push towards mid-off and calls his partner through for a single
short and wide, was there for the cut, but he is maybe slightly late on it and the ball rises over his top edge
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: far more controlled this time, chops the ball down to point. This one didn't bounce as much, and the line was a little closer to the batsman
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: this one isn't quite short enough to cut, and it comes back in late to sneak past the inside edge
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: full-toss, and that must hurt. Fast, at the batsman, and swinging in late. Looks to flick it hurriedly and only manages an inside-edge onto the inside of his left thigh
Commentary_short: Starc to Azhar Ali, no run

Commentary: low full-toss on off stump, jams his bat down to block to mid-on
Commentary_short: Starc to Azhar Ali, no run

Commentary: another full-toss, low, but this one is way outside off stump. Azhar reaches out, meets it with a horizontal bat, and stabs it to the right of the diving Maxwell at backward point
Commentary_short: Starc to Azhar Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: gone! Full, swinging in, and it's so hard to drag your front leg away from those. He's forced to play across it, misses it by a long way, and he doesn't bother reviewing. I'd like to see ball-tracking anyway - seemed like there was just a bit of a chance it may have swung down the leg side. Nope. Hitting the middle of leg stump, it says
Dismissal_text: Azhar Ali lbw b Starc 6 (12m 8b 1x4 0x6) SR: 75.00

Commentary: fullish, close to off stump, defended to mid-off, shows the full face
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: very full, wide of off, opens his bat face to jab it to third man
length ball, was looking for the one that swings away from the line of the stumps, but it doesn't swing and ends up going down the leg side
this one does swing, just a little, starts on a fifth-stump line and Babar leaves it alone
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full, close to off stump, Babar shows the full face of his bat to punch down the ground, to the left of mid-on
back of a length, a bit of swing towards middle stump to cramp Sharjeel. Defended back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: is that another lbw? Simon Fry says no. Full, and from that angle it needs to be full to get the left-hander. Nope, pitching outside leg and probably missing too. Looks to flick it and the swing beats his edge
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, jabbed to mid-on
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: shot! That's a length ball, but he's offered just a bit of width, and he sets himself up on a lovely stable base and lets his arms flow through the line of the ball to send it racing between cover and mid-off
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball close to off stump, defended into the covers
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: low full-toss on middle stump, moves his front leg out of the way to account for the swing and brings a straight bat down to clip to the right of mid-on
short, cramps up Sharjeel as he shapes to pull. Only manages a feeble swat to square leg
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: and again, shortish ball cramping Sharjeel for room. Ends up hitting him on the body as he tries to tuck it into the leg side
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: And again. Sharjeel is too closed-off against this shortish ball angling into his body, and it ends up hitting him on his uplifted thigh
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: fullish, close to off stump, pushed into the point region
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: length ball on off stump, punched to mid-on
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: length ball on off stump, delivers from slightly wider of the crease, defended back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full, down the leg side. Can't connect with the flick
fullish, close to off stump, defended into the covers
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: fullish outside off, driven on the up to mid-off
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: drags his length back slightly, Babar gets forward to defend into the covers
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: ooh, excellent ball. Full outside off, wider than the previous balls, but not a half-volley. Reaches away from his body to drive and it straightens to take his edge, runs away down to third man
full on off stump, check-driven to the left of mid-off

short, angling into the body, and this time Sharjeel times his swivel to get his body out of the way and bring his bat around to pull to the midwicket boundary. Toe-ended it, but at least he met it with his bat this time
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off stump, a bit of away swerve, punched back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Starc to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, clipped to the right of the diving midwicket fielder
short outside off, maybe not enough width to cut. Jabs at it instead, looking to hit through point or maybe to third man, and the ball bounces extra and beats his edge
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, driven firmly but too close to mid-off, who stops it with a tumble to his right
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump. Sharjeel plays it with an angled bat and dabs towards short third man
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: full now, overpitched, and Sharjeel puts it away, meets it with a nice, free swing of his bat to send it running away between cover and cover point
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length close to off stump, and that's nicely played, whipped against the angle to the left of long-on
short, wide, slashed away to the left of a desperately diving backward point fielder
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: short and wide again, beaten this time. May have connected with the cut had he moved his back foot across a little quicker
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: bouncer over off stump, Sharjeel is beaten for pace as he tries to hook this. Top-edge loops up dangerously but lands a fair distance from the man running towards the boundary from short fine leg
fullish, angling towards middle stump from over the wicket. Sharjeel defends back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Cummins to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: once again, fullish and attacking the stumps. Sharjeel lets it come on, meets it with soft hands, and drops it into the off side for a quick single
back of a length outside off, punched to the left of mid-off

full on off stump, driven back straight and Cummins asks for a run-out. He thinks he's got a hand on it to deflect the ball into the stumps. Was Babar inside his crease? Let's see what the replays say. Looks like there was the tiniest touch of the fingertip... but Babar has stretched back and made his ground comfortably.
Commentary_short: Cummins to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: shortish, not enough width to cut, can't play it as square as he'd like, straight to the fielder at cover point
Commentary_short: Cummins to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: length ball close to off stump, pushed gently towards cover-point, who's right on the edge of the circle, and Sharjeel picks up another sharp single
starts with a short ball on off stump, pulled to deep square leg
back of a length close to off stump, blocked back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: length ball slanting across the stumps. Wants to drive through cover but the ball doesn't quite come on, and he ends up inside-edging into his pads
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched to cover point
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, opens up a touch to be able to whip this to deep midwicket
full on off and middle, and that's an excellent shot, flicks it in the air, in the gap to the right of midwicket, and beats the fielder running to his left from long-on
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length, some inward movement towards off stump to cramp Babar. Wants to punch through the covers, can only play it back to the bowler in the end
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: ooh. Having brought the previous ball back in, he gets this to straighten. A little fuller, and Babar pushes forward at it without getting a big stride in, and it beats the outside edge of his defensive bat
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length, swinging in just a bit towards off stump. Lets it come on and dabs towards point
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: length ball outside off, and that's a lovely shot, driven on the up between cover point and cover, and Warner chases back from cover and dives full-length to pull it back from the rope
shortish, rising over middle stump. Babar shuffles across to whip it away through square leg
bouncer, Babar ducks under it
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short outside off, slapped away to deep point
back of a length on off stump, punched back firmly to the bowler
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short outside off, and that's a super shot. Packed off-side field on the 30-yard circle, and he gets on top of the bounce and slaps it away to the left of cover point
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, shuffles across to work it to deep square leg
fullish on off stump, gets forward to block to cover
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: shortish, close to off stump, and that's well played. A whip-pull with front leg raised to send it speeding away to the square leg boundary
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: oooh, whatashot! Full, angling into off stump, and Babar just meets it with the full face showing and drives to the left of mid-on
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: short outside off, lets it come on and rolls his wrists over at the top of the bounce to steer it down to third man
shortish on middle stump, Sharjeel works it away through square leg
length ball on off stump, defended into the off side
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, straightens just a touch. Wanted to work that into the leg side, but checked himself and didn't close his bat face in the end. Adjusted to the movement by playing with a straight bat towards cover
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short, angling into off and middle. Hops to get on top of the bounce and defends into the off side
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tossed up on middle stump, driven to mid-off
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: length ball on off stump, blocked back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: full on middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket
back of a length on off stump. Wants to punch that to long-on but short midwicket moves quickly to intercept
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: shot! That's a full ball outside off, and he's pretty much square-cut that, picks up two towards deep point
tossed up outside off, gets forward for a checked punch to short cover
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short of a length and angling away outside off, 146ks, steered down to third man for a single
dug short and outside off, 140.4ks, Babar camps back and swats it away to Starc running around at deep square leg
short and outside off, bursts off the surface, jumps over Sharjeel's attempted upper-cut
Commentary_short: Cummins to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: fractionally short and outside off, Sharjeel loves it there. He leans back and scythes a cut to the left of diving backward point. Whistles away to the fence
Commentary_short: Cummins to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length and sliding away outside off, Sharjeel rides the bounce and nudges a single down to third man
back of a length and holds its line outside off, crisply punched on the back foot past Maxwell's right at backward point. He dives and takes some pace off the ball
full on middle, no turn, easily driven to long-off
spins into the pads, whipped along the ground to deep square leg
shorter legbreak outside off, Azam moves back and punches it to the left of Zampa
loopier on middle, non-turning ball, bunted to midwicket
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: chipped just over the head of mid-off.... and rolls away to the boundary. Tossed-up legbreak outside off, dips, creating some distance between the bat and the pitch. Sharjeel goes through with the lofted drive and ends up chipping in the air. He could have been out. Instead, gets a boundary
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: spinning into the hips, short-arm pulled away to deep square leg
drops it short and outside off, Sharjeel goes back and chops to point
Commentary_short: Head to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: short and outside off again, this is flat-batted away to long-off
tossed up on the pads from around the wicket, nurdled to square leg
Commentary_short: Head to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: whipped off the pads through the vacant spaces at midwicket. There's protection in the deep
full and slides on middle, driven down to long-off. Three half-centuries in a row for Sharjeel
down the track, Azam gets close enough to the pitch and drives a single down to long-on
dragged down on middle, camps back and forces the ball to mid-on
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: length ball outside off, Babar throws his hands at the ball and inside-edges the ball just past off stump
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: slides on, flat and outside off, eased down to long-off
fired down the leg side, the ball bobbles out of Wade's gloves, and they sneak across
tossed up full on off, driven to extra cover
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: nice and full, non-turning break on middle, driven down to long-off
slower legbreak, turns in, nurdled to midwicket with soft hands
looped up outside off, Sharjeel scoops up in the air, in front of long-off
pushed through flatter as Azam comes down the track and works a single to long-on
dropped fractionally short and outside off, Sharjeel is really quick to skip back and put it over midwicket with a pull
Commentary_short: Head to Sharjeel Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: short offbreak outside off, goes back and lashes a square-cut to deep point
full and slides across off, driven in the gap at extra cover
short and wide outside off, Sharjeel goes deep in the crease as flat-bats a cut to sweeper on the off side
tossed up on middle and leg spins down the leg side, Sharjeel goes low and paddles it fine of Faulkner, I think, at short fine leg for the century stand
length-ball legbreak, driven to the left of extra cover
slides on flatter and quicker, this time he mis-times a drive straight to extra cover
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: another quick, flat legbreak, which is slashed away to point
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: dropped short and wide outside off, Azam is quick to rock back and cut to sweeper
flighted on the leg stump, swept straight to Faulkner at short fine leg
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: back of a length and slanted in, picked off through midwicket
full and wide outside off, flat-batted away to the right of mid-off
wide of the crease and angles a short ball into a back-foot punch to mid-on
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on off, Azam hangs back, twirls his wrists and flicks smartly through midwicket
slower ball outside off or on off, back of the hand, shovelled away with the bottom hand to long-on
length ball outside off, opens the face, and runs it away towards backward point. You can't take on Maxwell's arm
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tossed up very slower through the air on off, 79ks, Sharjeel sizes it up and swings it over midwicket, clears Starc in the deep
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, SIX runs

Commentary: Zampa dives to his right and deflects the ball back onto the stumps, appeals, but Babar is in. Tossed-up legbreak, nearly scooped back to the bowler. The ball just dies in front of him. Babar backed up, but is back by the time the bail comes off the groove
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: change-up, quicker, hurrying ball. Defended
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: slides on the leg stump, slog-swept away square of short fine leg
shorter legbreak, turns away outside off, Babar goes hard on the cut, loses his shape, and chops the ball square on the off side
Zampa throws it up outside off, Sharjeel takes it on. He opens up his shoulders, swings it mightily across the line and dumps Zampa over the wide long-on fence
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, SIX runs

Commentary: back of a length and outside off, front-foot punch to Cooper at mid-off
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length and wide outside off, Azam scythes a back-foot cut and finds point
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tight line just a shade outside off, opens the face and runs the ball to point. Three dots after a 14-run over
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: dug short on middle, swatted straight down the ground with a flat bat
very full and wide outside off, Sharjeel crunches a drive on the up to Starc at deep point
back of the hand slower ball outside off, tapped away through point. Just four off the over after 14 off the previous one
legbreak, dragged short and turns outside off, stands tall and punches to long-off
full and straight, Sharjeel plays back and flicks past midwicket's left. Smith chases the ball, slides and tests his ankle out
another shorter legbreak outside off, back-foot force to deep point
lobbed up outside off, turns away, Sharjeel reads the wrong'un. The length was short, which helped Sharjeel, and he punched to long-off on the back foot
sliding into the leg stump, punched down to long-on
pushed through flat on middle and leg, not much turn, camps back and punchily blocks back to Zampa
Commentary_short: Zampa to Sharjeel Khan, no run

Commentary: pitched up and angling away outside off, gets forward and drives it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: yorker, slanting away outside off, Babar can't jam it out
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: inswinging yorker on middle and leg, squirted to mid-on

Starc returns and bounces out Sharjeel. Wade sensibly moves to his right and tracks down the skier with the big gloves. Starc runs in hard and hits the deck harder. Rapid chest-high short delivery just outside off. Sharjeel is late onto the hook and skies a catch to Wade
Dismissal_text: Sharjeel Khan c †Wade b Starc 79 (105m 69b 9x4 2x6) SR: 114.49

Commentary: full and angling away, driven past Starc's right to mid-on
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: quick lifter on the leg stump, Azam watches it carefully and ducks under it. Only nine off the last three overs. Sharjeel fell to the scoreboard pressure
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: Zampa hangs it up in the air, full on middle, pushed back down the pitch
might have been a googly, zips in, inside-edged onto the pad, Azam weathers the lbw appeal
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short and wide outside off, cracked on the back foot to sweeper for a fifty
non-turning legbreak, which is calmly push-driven to long-off on the front foot
looped up on middle, chipped to long-off
short legbreak, turns away outside off, the batsman gets on top of it and flays a cut to deep point
nice and full on off, 145.3ks, defended
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: ripping yorker on off, 146.6ks, squeezed back to the bowler, who has an aim at the stumps
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: good length and slanting away outside off, 147.4ks, Hafeez drives away from the body and sends an outside edge flying to the left of Smith. Starc comes back and what does he do? Takes two wickets in space of six balls and jolts the chase
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Hafeez c Smith b Starc 3 (8m 6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: back of a length on middle, 145.9ks, played back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Starc to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: slightly overpitched and outside off, Malik leans into a drive and finds extra cover
Commentary_short: Starc to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: bouncer, angling away outside off, Malik drops his wrists on it
Commentary_short: Starc to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: tossed up on middle, full, Babar stays leg-side of the ball and drives it inside-out over extra cover. Beats long-off in the deep. Excellent execution
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and straight on middle, gets forward and pushes it back to Zampa
Commentary_short: Zampa to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: down the track and mis-times a drive to cover
length-ball legbreak outside off. Malik goes back and guides through point
slides on, very full on middle, driven down to long-off on the front foot
turning legbreak outside off, Malik gropes outside off with no feet and watches the ball pass the outside edge
Commentary_short: Zampa to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: full and outside off, Azam opens the face of the bat and drives it to the left of sweeper cover. Handscomb runs across and lets it the ball through to the boundary
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: very full and just a shade outside leg, misses the pad, misses leg stump. Wide
back of a length and outside off, carves a drive to Handscomb, who mops it up in the deep
very full and angling away outside off, 145.9ks, squeezes a drive to Cummins at extra cover
short on leg stump, Azam shuffles inside the line and just deflects the ball down to fine leg
short on middle, hops and fends the ball through square leg. Hares back for the second

full and angling away outside off, drives in front of mid-off, and sets off does Malik. Warner is on the prowl, swoops down on the ball, diving forward, but can't throw the stumps down at the non-striker's end
short of a length and outside off, Malik goes back, rides the bounce and punches to deep point
short on off, hops and deflects the ball behind square on the off side
shot. Babar sends the white ball sailing over mid-on who is inside the circle. Length and outside off, lofts it over the in-field with authority
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, SIX runs

Commentary: short and outside off, shuffles across off and pulls to deep square leg
back of a length and outside off, opens the face and dabs the ball to the right of Smith at wide slip
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: big short ball outside off, a bit too quick for Malik. He hooks and top-edges it over the head of Wade behind the stumps
full on the stumps, chips a drive in front of Starc at mid-on
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: bouncer, flies off the surface, over the upright batsman. Wide
nice and full outside off, gets forward, meets the pitch and drives in the direction of Handscomb at sweeper
back of a length on middle, camps back and flicks through the midwicket region. Pakistan pass David Warner's 179
length ball outside off, 146.4ks, opens the face and glides down to third man

appeal for caught behind? Did that loop off the arm or glove behind to Smith running back and across to his right at wide slip. Skiddy short ball, leaps off the surface, angled in, Malik was probably not sure whether to duck or fend. In the end, he does a bit of both, and also takes his eyes off the ball. The ball pings his forearm and loops over to slip. Malik clutches his wrist in pain. Australia did well not to review it. The physio is out to attend to Malik
Commentary_short: Cummins to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: short of a length and angled in, Umar jumps off the ground and fends it just beside the pitch on the leg side. Cummins runs in and across to his right, attacks the ball, picks it and aims a throw at the striker's end. Umar, who was searching for a risky single - there wasn't a single there actually - spins back and survives. Babar does not move. A direct hit could have had him
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: leg-side ball, deflected to long leg
length and outside off, helped down to third man
back of a length and outside off, punched on the up, straight to short extra cover
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: chest-high short ball outside off, swivels on the back foot, rides the bounce. Pulls to long leg
takes a short ball from outside off and swats it away to deep midwicket on the back foot
full on middle and leg, shuffles across off and clips it away to the right of deep square leg
length ball, kicks up outside off, Umar has a loose waft away from the body and does not make contact. His feet went nowhere
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: short and outside off, rolls his wrists and pulls a single to long leg
just short of a good length and outside off, slower one, angled down to third man
length and outside off, opens the face, and guides past backward point to third man
short and down leg, ducks under it. Wide called
Babar shuffles across off, meets a hip-high short ball on middle, not sure if he inside-edged it onto the thigh
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short of a length and outside off, swatted away to the left of deep midwicket
back of a length, skids on, beats the batsman's attempt to flick to leg and raps the thigh
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: length ball on middle, slower, Umar eyes a leg-side pick up and is hit on the box
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: back of a length and outside off, stands up tall and punches to sweeper cover

Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: short of a length and outside off, leans back and cuts to the right of third man
full on middle and leg, picked up and flicked in the air over backward square leg
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball outside off, chipped in the air straight down the ground
just short of a good length on off, hops and chops to point
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: length and outside off, deftly run down to third man
high bouncer outside off, the batsman drops his wrists on it. Not a wide. Cummins gets away
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: back of a length and outside off, 143ks, guided down to third man for one more
short on middle, 146ks, hustles the batsman for pace. More of a short-arm flap than a short-arm pull. The ball goes only as far as midwicket
Commentary_short: Cummins to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: back of a length on middle and leg, tucked away into the midwicket region
slower ball, full on off stump, driven with a lot of power but hit straight to mid-off
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: shortish, too much width, slapped away to the point boundary and Babar moves into the 90s
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: short again, down the leg side this time, and that's terrible bowling with fine leg in the circle. Whip-pulled away to the left of the fielder and it races for another four
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: loopy slower ball wide of off stump, and that's superbly played by Babar, just reaches out and meets it with an open bat face to steer it to the right of backward point
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length close to off stump, lets it come on and pushes into the point region to move to 99
length ball, wide of off, well wide in fact. Reaches out to drive and plays and misses. Called wide, and on replay it's clear it was wide of the tramline

there's the hundred, it's been a superb innings so far. Back of a length on off stump, and he tucks it quietly through square leg to pick up one. Not too much of a celebration. Takes his helmet off, raises his bat to the crowd, hugs his cousin at the other end, and gets back to business
back of a length on off stump, uses his wrists to play that to mid-on
fullish, and he gets this to swing away from a fifth-stump line to beat Babar's attempted on-the-up drive
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: there's that swing again, from the stumps this time, and Hazlewood's taken the big wicket. Looks to play a pick-up shot over mid-on, and that late swing meant he only got the leading edge to it, and the ball ballooned up for a simple catch to mid-on. An excellent delivery to end an excellent innings
Dismissal_text: Babar Azam c Head b Hazlewood 100 (153m 109b 7x4 1x6) SR: 91.74

Commentary: short, very wide outside off. Akmal reaches out to cut but can't connect
fullish outside off, defended to point
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, worked away to deep midwicket
back of a length, slanted across the right-hander. Akmal lets it come on and dabs to backward point
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, came back in slightly to cramp Akmal. Wanted to punch that through the covers, in the end he can only jam down his bat and squeeze it to backward point
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: length ball on middle stump, slogged away, on the bounce, to deep midwicket
back of a length close to off stump, opens his bat face to stab it down to third man

full on off stump, and that's dropped. Long-on was back, Akmal decided to take him on, and didn't get as much pace onto the bat as he'd have liked. Scooped it up, and Handscomb, running to his left and reaching overhead, got both hands to the ball but couldn't hold on
on the pads, clipped away through square leg
full, angling down leg. Rizwan can't connect with the flick
fullish, angling into off stump, driven firmly, beats cover diving to his right, but can't beat Warner, running to his left from mid-on
short, angling into the body, and that's excellent, swivelled to pull it from just in front of his chest, finds the gap between deep midwicket and long leg
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: ooh, what a follow-up. Back of a length, angling into off stump, straightening late. Opens up Akmal and beats his outside edge as he looks to defend, feet rooted to the spot
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: fullish on off stump, and that's a safe shot now that mid-on and midwicket are in the circle. Doesn't really middle this slog, but gets it safely over the gap between the two fielders

shot! That's a length ball angling into off stump, nothing too wrong with it, considering the movement he's getting. Brings his bottom hand into play and whips it wristily over the gap to mid-on's left
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball on off stump, punched back to the bowler, who sees Akmal out of his crease and fires a throw that narrowly misses off stump
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: short, rising ball angling into the body. Jumps to ride the bounce and knocks it down into the leg side with soft hands
slower ball outside off, Akmal slogs and misses
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: full, a little wider outside off, Akmal slices under the ball, halfway deliberately, to send it soaring into the air over the point region and it lands in the big gap to the right of third man
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: short outside off, looks like another slower ball. Akmal waits this time before dabbing it down to third man
bouncer, difficult one for Rizwan to negotiate, he has to hook from over his right shoulder. Top-edges and it loops over the keeper and lands in the gap to the right of long leg

short outside off, and that's timed too well for Rizwan's liking. Goes for the slash, ends up slicing under the ball, and does it carry to Starc diving forward from third man? He himself isn't sure. They're checking upstairs now... Soft signal is out. Looks like he's taken it cleanly. Yup, out, and is that it for Pakistan?
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Rizwan c Starc b Cummins 6 (16m 6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: length ball slanting away from off stump. Amir looks for the drive through cover, doesn't get forward quickly enough and he's comfortably beaten
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: this one's shorter, a little wider. Amir throws his bat at it but doesn't move his feet at all. Beaten again
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: shortish outside off, steered down to third man
back of a length outside off, sliced to third man
length ball close to off stump, driven through point with a slightly open face
back of a length outside off, lets it come on and dabs to third man
slower bouncer outside off, Akmal can't connect with the hook
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, another slower ball. This time Akmal holds his shape nicely, and swats it away to the wide long-on boundary
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: looks for the wide yorker, ends up bowling a fast, low, wide full-toss. Akmal uses the pace well, slices under it with an open face to send it screaming to the left of third man
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: This time he gets the wide yorker more or less on target. Akmal looks to reach out and squeeze it away, can't connect
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: slower full-toss on off stump, punched to sweeper cover
back of a length on middle stump, defended to cover
Commentary_short: Cummins to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot to sweeper cover

fullish on off stump, clears his front leg to slog, ends up dragging it along the ground to mid-on. An inaccurate shy at the bowler's end - from Cummins - gifts an overthrow, though Amir was out if he'd hit
slower length ball on middle and off. Looks to make room to slap through the off side, can't get it past cover
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: now he middles one. Fullish on middle stump, makes himself room again and lifts it over extra-cover
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Mohammad Amir, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on leg stump, driven with a lot of effort but straight to mid-on
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: shortish now, looks like another slower ball. Amir clears his front leg early, but then spots the change-up and holds his shape, and that allows him to time his swat over midwicket as sweetly as possible
Commentary_short: Hazlewood to Mohammad Amir, SIX runs

Commentary: slower ball, full and wide, and Akmal smacks it over mid-off. Picked his spot, and got exactly the delivery he needed. Cleared his front leg to make himself extra swinging room
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker on off stump, jabbed away to backward point and he wants a single. He's nearly halfway down the pitch before Amir sends him back. Makes his ground safely enough in the end
Commentary_short: Cummins to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: looks for the wide yorker, Akmal goes deep in his crease and across with his back foot to try and slap it through point, only manages a top-edge to the keeper
Dismissal_text: Umar Akmal c †Wade b Cummins 46 (59m 40b 7x4 0x6) SR: 115.00

Commentary: full, angling down leg. Can't connect with the flick and the ball hits him on the pad
Commentary_short: Cummins to Wahab Riaz, 1 leg bye

Commentary: that's the bouncer angled across Amir, and it's well played, kept his eye on it and then helped it over the keeper and slip, down to third man
full on off stump, driven crisply to sweeper cover
slower ball, leg-stumpish. Clears his front leg and gets down on one knee to swipe it through backward square leg
another slower ball, wide outside the left-hander's off stump. Amir slogs and misses
Commentary_short: Faulkner to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: loopy slower ball on middle stump, Amir makes room and slices it away to the left of short third man

back of a length slower ball on off stump. Amir makes room to slog, ends up hitting the high part of his bat and looping high in the air. Maxwell, the fielder at cover, runs in from the 30-yard circle and completes a simple catch
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Amir c Maxwell b Faulkner 17 (21m 14b 1x4 1x6) SR: 121.42

Commentary: slower ball wide of off, Wahab slashes and misses. Shamsuddin signals wide
another wide slower ball, fuller this time, slashed to the left of deep point
full on off stump, clears his front leg to flat-bat to long-off
middle-stump yorker, jams his bat down to dig it out
Commentary_short: Starc to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: full outside off. Wahab goes for the flashing drive, and can't connect
Commentary_short: Starc to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: low full-toss, almost hits the base of off stump on the full after Wahab clears his front leg and misses an ambitious drive
Commentary_short: Starc to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: very full outside off, Wahab plays and misses
Commentary_short: Starc to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: full outside off, sliced in the air, on the bounce, to the right of third man
full-toss outside off, and Hasan is off the mark with a nervy push that he edges. Bounces as it approaches Wade, and it hits his pad and runs away towards third man
slower ball at the batsman's legs. Gets down on one knee and slogs it away through square leg
length ball on middle stump, clipped to short fine leg
short on off stump, pulled in the air, one-bounce, to the right of long-on
loopy slower ball, full on off stump, pushed to mid-off
another slower ball, another full-blooded Wahab swipe, rolls along down to backward square leg
another slower ball. This time Hasan slogs, slices it high in the air, drops into the vacant mid-off region
full, slanting down leg. Misses the flick and it ricochets into the leg side off the pad
Commentary_short: Starc to Hasan Ali, 1 leg bye

Commentary: full on middle stump, Wahab clears his front leg and miscues a pick-up shot over mid-on. Just about clears the fielder
fullish on off stump, clears his front leg again, and this time meets it with a straight bat, shovels it back over the bowler's head
Commentary_short: Starc to Wahab Riaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: full-toss outside off, Wahab slices it over cover point, and Zampa, running in from the boundary and diving forward, gets both hands to it and spills it.
what is happening here? Full toss on off stump, looks to push towards mid-on and gets a leading edge that loops over short cover, to his left. Starc is furious
full outside off, Wahab has a big swing at it, and misses
Commentary_short: Starc to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: short ball, slides on with the angle to hit the batsman's thigh after he misses the pull
Commentary_short: Zampa to Hasan Ali, no run

Commentary: flighted outside off, Hasan goes for the slog-sweep and clears Maxwell, jumping to his right at the deep midwicket boundary
Commentary_short: Zampa to Hasan Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: down the track now, chips it on the bounce to sweeper cover
dangled up slow outside off, Wahab is too early into his slog-sweep, can't connect
Commentary_short: Zampa to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: this time it's too full for the slog-sweep, bottom-edges it to short fine leg
down the track comes Hasan, and Pakistan are eight down. Slowed it down, the tailender was through his slog well before it arrived, and then it spun away and offered Wade a simple stumping
